Me and my boyfriend waited for about 40 minutes to get in the restaurant which was no problem. Our first red flag was going to check in on our table and seeing that the man had already crossed our name out before calling us to notify our table was ready. The second red flag, came when we were seated. We were seated at the same time as another couple, but they were able to order first which again is perfectly fine.....but we then had to wait another 20-25 minutes to order. Once we finally got a chance to order, everyone else had already received their food. Still, me and my boyfriend waited patiently. We finally ordered and again by the time we got our food, everyone had already had 2 orders worth of food. Our final breaking point was when we received the food. We received the food, which wasn’t worth what we went through to get it, just to be forced to leave our skewer sticks all over the table because they didn’t bring us a bucket in the first place. They didn’t seem to care much about us, it showed on their face. My boyfriend expressed his disappointment to the man who I guess was running the restaurant, and he laughed in his face. Never again, so disappointed.
